Hungarian Stock Index Reverses Gains as Mol, OTP Shares Retreat

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-07-08T10:33:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-08/hungarian-stock-index-reverses-gains-as-mol-otp-shares-retreat.html
Hungary’s benchmark stock index fell,
erasing earlier gains as Mol Nyrt., the country’s biggest oil
refiner, and OTP Bank Nyrt., the largest lender, retreated.  The BUX gauge of 13 companies slid 0.4 percent to 22,400.77
by 12:10 p.m. in Budapest, after earlier rising as much as 0.6
percent. Mol, which has a 29 percent weighting in the index,
fell 1.5 percent to 20,600 forint.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  